										<content:encoded><![CDATA[		<div data-elementor-type="wp-post" data-elementor-id="838" class="elementor elementor-838 elementor-bc-flex-widget">
						<div class="elementor-inner">
				<div class="elementor-section-wrap">
									<section class="elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-54637b55 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default" data-id="54637b55" data-element_type="section">
						<div class="elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
							<div class="elementor-row">
					<div class="elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-4dd7c85a" data-id="4dd7c85a" data-element_type="column">
			<div class="elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated">
							<div class="elementor-widget-wrap">
						<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-1cb43a0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="1cb43a0" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
								<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
				<p>Is Hanoi worth visiting? Many people ask us this question when preparing their trip to Vietnam. For us, without a doubt<strong> </strong><strong>Hanoi is worth visiting</strong>. We fell in love with this city as soon as we arrived. The traffic is the first thing that  will caught your attention, as it really is madness! The quarters are beautiful and you can see Hanoi&#8217;s history through its buildings. People sitting outside and sipping coffee all day long. And no, we are not talking about any coffee&#8230;did you know that only the coffee already makes Hanoi worth visiting? It&#8217;s amazing!</p><h2 style="color: #7a7a7a;">How long should I stay?</h2><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">You can tick off the main attractions in 2 nights, but if you add another night you won&#8217;t regret it.</span> Also, Hanoi is the perfect base to do trips to <a href="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/2018/06/16/how-we-met-hill-tribes-of-sapa/">Sapa</a>, <a href="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/2018/06/19/ha-long-bay-or-sapa/">Ha Long Bay</a>, Ha Giang or Ninh Binh. Check our <a style="background-color: #ffffff;" href="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/2018/11/03/3-week-vietnam-itinerary/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">map with a 3 week itinerary </a>to see how to best move around.</p><h2 style="color: #7a7a7a;">How expensive is Hanoi?</h2><p>Another thing that makes Hanoi worth visiting is its terrific value. Some examples:</p>					</div>
						</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-36e6f1e elementor-align-left elementor-icon-list--layout-traditional elementor-list-item-link-full_width elementor-widget elementor-widget-icon-list" data-id="36e6f1e" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="icon-list.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<ul class="elementor-icon-list-items">
							<li class="elementor-icon-list-item">
											<span class="elementor-icon-list-icon">
																<i class="fa fa-bed" aria-hidden="true"></i>
													</span>
										<span class="elementor-icon-list-text">You can find budget accommodation for under 10$ the night, and for 15-20$ you'll get very comfortable and cool places</span>
									</li>
								<li class="elementor-icon-list-item">
											<span class="elementor-icon-list-icon">
																<i class="fa fa-coffee" aria-hidden="true"></i>
													</span>
										<span class="elementor-icon-list-text">Amazing Vietnamese coffee is under a dollar </span>
									</li>
								<li class="elementor-icon-list-item">
											<span class="elementor-icon-list-icon">
																<i class="fa fa-cutlery" aria-hidden="true"></i>
													</span>
										<span class="elementor-icon-list-text">Food ranges from 2$ to 4$ for local food and a bit more expensive for western dishes</span>
									</li>
								<li class="elementor-icon-list-item">
											<span class="elementor-icon-list-icon">
																<i class="fa fa-taxi" aria-hidden="true"></i>
													</span>
										<span class="elementor-icon-list-text">Taxis are crazy cheap if you use GRAB. A 5 minutes ride is about a dollar</span>
									</li>
						</ul>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-3a73409 elementor-widget elementor-widget-spacer" data-id="3a73409" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="spacer.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					<div class="elementor-spacer">
			<div class="elementor-spacer-inner"></div>
		</div>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-21248fa8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="21248fa8" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
								<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
				<p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: 'Nothing You Could Do'; font-size: 40px; font-weight: 900;">How to get from the airport</span></p><p>I know there are buses, but seriously, make yourself a favour and just get a <a href="https://r.grab.com/grabrafapiki">GRAB</a>. It is cheaper than the bus and more comfortable. We paid 10$ from the airport to the city centre.</p><h2>Where to stay</h2><h4><strong>Budget option: <a href="https://www.booking.com/hotel/vn/old-quarter-view-hanoi-hostel.en.html?aid=1593087&amp;no_rooms=1&amp;group_adults=1">Old Quarter View Hanoi Hostel</a></strong></h4><p>Located in the heart of the Old Quarter, it is the perfect hostel for backpackers. Comfort and value at the same time, it has options for<b> under 10$ a night, breakfast included.</b></p><p><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-992 aligncenter" src="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/142880944.jpg" alt="Budget hostel Hanoi" width="1200" height="900" srcset="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/142880944.jpg 1200w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/142880944-300x225.jpg 300w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/142880944-768x576.jpg 768w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/142880944-1024x768.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></p><h4>Comfort option: <a href="https://www.booking.com/hotel/vn/the-jasmine.en.html?aid=1593090&amp;no_rooms=1&amp;group_adults=1">Hanoi La Selva</a></h4><p>Great facilities and lovely staff at a very reasonable price. Gorgeous rooms and located in the Old Quarter, next to the <b>Hoan Kiem lake.</b></p><p><b><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-991 aligncenter" src="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/148970317.jpg" alt="Hanoi La Selva Hotel" width="1280" height="853" srcset="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/148970317.jpg 1280w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/148970317-300x200.jpg 300w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/148970317-768x512.jpg 768w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/148970317-1024x682.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /></b></p><h6> </h6><h3 style="text-align: left;"><span style="color: #808080;"><strong>Ok, what should I see?</strong></span></h3><h3>-Hoan Kiem Lake and Ngog Son</h3><p><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-983 aligncenter" src="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07854.jpg" alt="Temple on the Lake, Hanoi" width="2837" height="1910" srcset="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07854.jpg 2837w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07854-300x202.jpg 300w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07854-768x517.jpg 768w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07854-1024x689.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2837px) 100vw, 2837px" /></p><p>Hoan Kiem lake is one of the icons of Hanoi. Have a walk around and visit Ngog Son, a temple located on a small island in the middle of the lake. Once you&#8217;re done, please visit the &#8220;<a href="https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/Restaurant_Review-g293924-d3833551-Reviews-The_Note_Coffee-Hanoi.html">Note Coffee</a>&#8220;, just in the corner. It has a great variety of ice creams and coffee, and although it is a bit expensive for Vietnamese standards, it is well worth it.</p><p><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-982 aligncenter" src="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07828.jpg" alt="Bridge leading to the temple, Hanoi" width="2859" height="1812" srcset="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07828.jpg 2859w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07828-300x190.jpg 300w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07828-768x487.jpg 768w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07828-1024x649.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2859px) 100vw, 2859px" /></p><h3>-Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum</h3><p>A very interesting visit from a cultural and anthropological point of view. You will be sharing your visit with hundreds of North-Vietnamese, who daily show their respect for their leader. The ticket entrance also includes a visit to Ho Chi Minh&#8217;s old residence, gardens and even cars.</p><p><strong>TIP</strong>: Go early in the morning. Otherwise, you WILL queue for hours.</p><h3><strong>-Hoa Lo Prison</strong></h3><p>It was a prison used by the French colonists for Vietnamese political prisoners. Later, North Vietnam used it for U.S prisoners of war, such as the United States Senator John McCain. During this time, the prison got a new nickname: the Hanoi Hilton. We found a bit too much propaganda in the visit, but it is definitely a great place to learn more about Vietnam&#8217;s history.</p><h3>-Old Quarter</h3><div><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-987 aligncenter" src="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC07859-e1541936504493.jpg" alt="Old Quarter Hanoi" width="1395" height="1804" /></div><div> </div><p>The Old Quarter is the heart of Hanoi. All the markets are here, along with restaurants, old houses, museums, souvenirs shops, etc. Make sure you spend some quality time here but be aware that it can sometimes be a bit overwhelming. During the weekend, the main streets are closed at night and there is a night market.</p><p><strong>TIP</strong>: If you like homemade beer, visit Ta Hien Street, also known as beer street. One beer just 0.3$! YES, you read correctly!</p><h3>-Train street</h3><p>One of the most popular attractions of Hanoi. Two trains run daily along Le Duan and Kham Tien streets. The street is very narrow and people actually live there, so don&#8217;t be surprised if you find people sitting on a chair having their lunch on the railway or chickens running around.</p><p><strong>TIP</strong>: The trains passes at 3.30pm and 7.30pm. Make sure you arrive a bit earlier to grab a nice spot!</p><h3><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-984 aligncenter" src="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC08470.jpg" alt="Train Street , Hanoi" width="1952" height="2447" srcset="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC08470.jpg 1952w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC08470-239x300.jpg 239w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC08470-768x963.jpg 768w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/DSC08470-817x1024.jpg 817w" sizes="(max-width: 1952px) 100vw, 1952px" /></h3><h3> </h3><h3>Other places in Hanoi worth visiting&#8230;</h3><p><strong>-Wander around the</strong> <strong>French Quarter</strong> and enjoy the architecture</p><p><strong>-Don Xuan Market.</strong> You can find pretty much anything here. Prices are good but be aware that sellers aren&#8217;t particularly nice, we discovered this the hard way!</p><p><strong>-Museum of Anthropology</strong>. Especially interesting if you want to know about the different tribes that live in the North of Vietnam. Did you know there are at least 54 ethnic minorities, each with its own language, lifestyle, and cultural heritage?</p><p><strong>-Water puppet theater</strong></p><p><strong>-Opera house</strong></p><h2>Ok ok, too much sightseeing&#8230;what about trying something different?</h2><p>One of our best experiences was doing a food tour of <a href="https://www.hanoifreewalkingtours.com/">https://www.hanoifreewalkingtours.com/</a>. Brian, a university student from Hanoi, helped us to <strong>discover Vietnamese cuisine</strong>. We visited 5 different restaurants, and some of them were places that you probably wouldn&#8217;t visit on your own. The food was in general delicious and it was very nice to get to know someone local.</p><p><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-985 aligncenter" src="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IMG_20180516_193611.jpg" alt="Free food tour in Hanoi, check our post!" width="1252" height="729" srcset="https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IMG_20180516_193611.jpg 1252w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IMG_20180516_193611-300x175.jpg 300w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IMG_20180516_193611-768x447.jpg 768w, https://rafagf.github.io/itfeelsgoodtobelost/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IMG_20180516_193611-1024x596.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1252px) 100vw, 1252px" /></p><p>The tour is FREE. You obviously pay for all the food (less than 15$), including your guide&#8217;s. A tip is also appreciated. You won&#8217;t regret doing the tour and it will make your trip to Vietnam easier as you will know what to order from this point.</p><p>Sooo, what are you waiting for to visit Hanoi?</p>					</div>
